12b/n Folks are overlooking just how effective this new & improved $GME team has been. A few more quarters of execution & many investors will come around to the idea that this star-studded management, board, & investor base is not only competent, but outstanding.

11b/n $GME Since physical sales decline in later yrs of cycle (thus digital % rises), I suspect that‚Äôs been interfering w/ folks‚Äô analysis of the physical/digital mix. This will be more apparent in ~12mo when people realize how heavily folks lean physical in these early years

11a/n And only now do we return to $GME's trade-in business. Everyone agrees the shift to digital is happening, but it‚Äôs happening much slower than everyone appreciates for many reasons (preference, resale value, sharing, storage/speeds, gifts, etc.)

10/n $GME is also the best in the biz when it comes to adding value for vendors, esp in the early years of cycle. Ex: sizable market share, industry-leading attachment rates, expert sales force. See this SA article for some additional examples: https://t.co/SsZ1HGO1n4

9/n Then we return to $GME's legacy business, which is likely to thrive in coming yrs. Dramatic cost-cutting, a massively revamped omnichannel experience (see $BBY for proof B&M can work), & fact that gamers prefer physical over digital in early yrs of cycle is recipe for success

8/n On the merchandising front $GME is now more aggressively pursuing PC gaming & accessories. This is a major opportunity because these are higher margin products and $GME is poised to participate meaningfully in this space given its scale and complementary offerings

7/n More valuable is 60m PowerUp members‚Äìthis likely attracted Cohen to $GME. Per Wissink: This gamer DB of spending/behavior data is the only cross platform dataset of size. GME could create a high margin, ad-targeting platform to improve ad efficacy for vendors...$600m in EBIT

6/n Seems likely that we‚Äôll soon hear from $GME about similar partnerships with firms like $SNE, $NTDOY, $ATVI, $EA, etc. Ex via Preston: Game publishers spend up to $300m marketing blockbuster games; could make sense to partner w/ $GME to showcase games or try out new concepts
